    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Printmaking technique in which the plate is painted directly with acid, so that the artist is drawing with acid rather than ink; the acid is washed off when the desired effect had been achieved. Technique is typically used with etching, rather than as the sole technique.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
